{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17585849","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17585849"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T08:20:03+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T08:20:03+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15023"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15023","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15023"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.18,0.06,0.27,0.27,0.21]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7711"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65879"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7711","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7711"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15023"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51324"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4933"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4943"},{"type":"tags","id":"7607"},{"type":"tags","id":"9877"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"18840"},{"type":"contributions","id":"18843"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65879","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/65879"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EAntidiuretic hormone (ADH) secretion from the posterior pituitary is regulated by multiple physiological and pharmacological factors.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following increases antidiuretic hormone secretion?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Alcohol","Haloperidol","Increased blood pressure","Clonidine","Carbamazepine"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EADH secretion is primarily regulated by two physiological mechanisms: plasma osmolality (via osmoreceptors) and blood volume/pressure (via baroreceptors). Various drugs and hormones can modify these basic control mechanisms.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAlcohol\u003C/strong\u003E is a potent inhibitor of ADH secretion, which leads to increased diuresis. \u003Cstrong\u003EHaloperidol\u003C/strong\u003E has no significant direct effect on ADH secretion. \u003Cstrong\u003EIncreased blood pressure\u003C/strong\u003E activates baroreceptors which inhibit ADH release as part of volume homeostasis. \u003Cstrong\u003EClonidine\u003C/strong\u003E, an alpha-2 agonist, does not significantly affect ADH secretion.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECarbamazepine\u003C/strong\u003E stimulates ADH release through direct effects on the hypothalamus. This effect can contribute to water retention and hyponatraemia in some patients taking this medication.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Carbamazepine stimulates antidiuretic hormone (ADH) release via direct effects on the hypothalamus","Alcohol and increased blood pressure inhibit ADH release","ADH secretion is primarily regulated by plasma osmolality and blood volume/pressure"],"references":["Sparapani S, Millet-Boureima C, Oliver J, Mu K, Hadavi P, Kalostian T, Ali N, Avelar CM, Bardies M, Barrow B, Benedikt M, Biancardi G, Bindra R, Bui L, Chihab Z, Cossitt A, Costa J, Daigneault T, Dault J, Davidson I, Dias J, Dufour E, El-Khoury S, Farhangdoost N, Forget A, Fox A, Gebrael M, Gentile MC, Geraci O, Gnanapragasam A, Gomah E, Haber E, Hamel C, Iyanker T, Kalantzis C, Kamali S, Kassardjian E, Kontos HK, Le TBU, LoScerbo D, Low YF, Mac Rae D, Maurer F, Mazhar S, Nguyen A, Nguyen-Duong K, Osborne-Laroche C, Park HW, Parolin E, Paul-Cole K, Peer LS, Philippon M, Plaisir CA, Porras Marroquin J, Prasad S, Ramsarun R, Razzaq S, Rhainds S, Robin D, Scartozzi R, Singh D, Fard SS, Soroko M, Soroori Motlagh N, Stern K, Toro L, Toure MW, Tran-Huynh S, Tr\u00e9panier-Chicoine S, Waddingham C, Weekes AJ, Wisniewski A, Gamberi C. The Biology of Vasopressin. Biomedicines. 2021 Jan 18;9(1):89. doi: 10.3390/biomedicines9010089. PMID: 33477721; PMCID: PMC7832310.","Yasir M, Mechanic OJ. Syndrome of Inappropriate Antidiuretic Hormone Secretion. [Updated 2023 Mar 6]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK507777/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51324"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15023"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51324","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/51324"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-27T12:10:14+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-27T12:11:52+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7711"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65879"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying a